==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oblongum
<hw>Ob*lon"gum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Oblonga</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Oblong</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A prolate spheroid; a
figure described by the revolution of an ellipse about its greater axis.
Cf. <er>Oblatum</er>, and see <cref>Ellipsoid of revolution</cref>,
under <er>Ellipsoid</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obloquious</ent>⟦br⟧
